<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12">
        <div class="wrapper wrapper-content animated fadeInUp">
            <div class="ibox">
                <div class="ibox-content">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-12">
                            <p> All incidents are to be recorded in an Incident Report within 24 hours of the occurrence, even if assumed to be of minor severity. <b>  Incident Reports must be prepared for all happenings that are outside of normal daily property activities, even if you have doubt around the situation.</b> All incidents are important, no matter how minor it may seem.  When in doubt, file a report. </p>
                            <p> Any photographs and supporting documents from local authorities or residents/claimants should be uploaded as available and added to the incident report portal after initial submission of the incident report.   </p>
                            <br />
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <span class="romnum"> i. </span>	<b> When should Employees complete Incident Reports?  </b> <br />
                                  <p>  <b>EVERY TIME </b> an incident occurs within the community.  Examples of scenarios requiring an Incident Report:  personal injury (residents or vendors; <b>  Property Managers should file a workers compensation claim for employees experiencing injury)</b>, death, fire, burglary, assault, property damage, storm damage, insect damage or situations of similar magnitude.  </p>

                                    </li>
                                <li>
                                    <span class="romnum"> ii. </span>  <b>   How should an employee respond to incidents? </b>
                                    <p>
                                        All employees should maintain composure and act in a professional manner.  Suggested practices to moderate a stressful situation are as follows:
                                    </p>

                                    <ul>
                                        <li> Speak in a normal tone. Do not raise the volume of your voice. </li>
                                        <li> Think logically when evaluating the plan of action. Do not act on impulse. </li>
                                        <li> Consider any immediate safety measures that may need to be taken. </li>
                                        <li> If the individual involved does not wish to file a police report and one is needed, the Property Manager must take initiative and do so </li>
                                        <li> Ensure all pertinent and factual details are documented, recorded and retained. Refrain from giving opinions or adding speculative comments.  Once the report is filed, you may be requested to provide more information.</li>
                                    </ul>

                                </li>
                               
                            </ul>

                            <br />
                            <h2> <b> Regarding Specific Emergencies and guidance around action and reporting,  </b> </h2><p> please see the <span style="font-style:italic">  Emergency Procedures Manual </span> available in digital searchable format located in Carroll Connect.  There you will find detailed information on specific reportable subjects, such as: </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li> Accident or Medical Emergency (policy #5060) </li>
                                <li> Slips, Trips and Falls (policy #5065) </li>
                                <li> Theft/Robbery (policy #5120) </li>
                                <li> Death or Suspected Death (policy #5095) </li>
                                <li> Assault or Criminal Act Against and Individual (policy #5125) </li>
                                <li> Vandalism (policy #5115) </li>
                                <li> Fire (policy #5150) </li>
                                <li> Storms – General (policy #5160) </li>
                                <li> After an Emergency (policy #5205) </li>



                            </ul>

                            <p> <b> As a reminder, if ever in doubt regarding reportable items or the need to relay important safety information to residents, please reach out to your Regional Manager and/or the corporate Operations team for additional assistance.</b>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
